Qualcomm ($QCOM) had a strong day, Thursday, as the communication chipmaker's shares climbed more than 3% in the wake of the company claiming a victory in a patent dispute with Apple (NASDAQ:AAPL).
On Wednesday, the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit said in a 2-to-1 ruling that Apple ($AAPL) can't revive a challenge to Qualcomm's (QCOM) mobile-phone patents due to a settlement that was already reached between the tech giants. It was the second time this year that Apple's (AAPL) challenges to the settlement had been rejected in federal court

The matter dates back to 2017, when Qualcomm (QCOM) sued Apple (AAPL) for patent infringement regarding technologies used in iPhone, iPads and Apple Watches. The companies eventually reached a settlement in the matter in 2019 that allowed Apple (AAPL) to keep using Qualcomm (QCOM) in its devices
